SIMPLE: net
RECORDS: 5

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Net
<hw>Net</hw> <pr>(n⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>net</ets>;
akin to D. <ets>net</ets>, OS. <ets>net</ets>, <ets>netti</ets>, OHG.
<ets>nezzi</ets>, G. <ets>netz</ets>, Icel. & Dan. <ets>net</ets>, Sw.
<ets>n⟦aum⟧t</ets>, Goth. <ets>nati</ets>; of uncertain origin.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A fabric of twine, thread, or the like, wrought or
woven into meshes, and used for catching fish, birds, butterflies,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything designed or fitted to entrap or catch; a
snare; any device for catching and holding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man that flattereth his neighbor spreadeth a <qex>net</qex> for
his feet.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. xxix. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the church's <qex>net</qex> there are fishes good or bad.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything wrought or woven in meshes; <as>as, a
<ex>net</ex> for the hair; a mosquito <ex>net</ex>; a tennis
<ex>net</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A figure made up of a large
number of straight lines or curves, which are connected at certain
points and related to each other by some specified law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A network.</def> <mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>The internet; --
usually <altname>the net</altname>; <as>as, I found it on the
<ex>net</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Net</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Net
<hw>Net</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Netted</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Netting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make into a net;
to make in the style of network; <as>as, to <ex>net</ex>
silk</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take in a net; to capture by stratagem or
wile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And now I am here, <qex>netted</qex> and in the toils.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To inclose or cover with a net; <as>as, to
<ex>net</ex> a tree</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Net</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Net
<hw>Net</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To form network or netting; to
knit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Net</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Net
<hw>Net</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. See <er>Neat</er> clean.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Without spot; pure; shining.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her breast all naked as <qex>net</qex> ivory.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Free from extraneous substances; pure;
unadulterated; neat; <as>as, <ex>net</ex> wine, etc.</as></def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not including superfluous, incidental, or foreign
matter, as boxes, coverings, wraps, etc.; free from charges, deductions,
etc; <as>as, <ex>net</ex> profit; <ex>net</ex> income; <ex>net</ex>
weight, etc.</as></def> <altsp>[Less properly written
<asp>nett</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Net tonnage</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>the tonnage
of a vessel after a deduction from the gross tonnage has been made, to
allow space for crew, machinery, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Net</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Net
<hw>Net</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Netted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Netting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To produce or gain as clear
profit; <as>as, he <ex>netted</ex> a thousand dollars by the
operation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Netball</ent>⟦br⟧
